HEADWORD: Intercrural
<hw>In`ter*cru"ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Between crura; -- applied especially to the interneural plates in
the vertebral column of many cartilaginous fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

